- 2.0.2 | Mar 02 2026:
  [Fix] Validate SCAN_MAX_LINES, SCAN_TIMEOUT, and max_lines arguments in
      tlog_read_full() and tlog_journal_read_full() — non-numeric values
      default to 0 (no limit/no timeout) with stderr warning; prevents
      silent wrong behavior from bash arithmetic coercion (F-002)
  [Fix] --status subcommand: correctly display corrupt cursor state instead
      of showing "not initialized"; show raw cursor content for diagnosis
      (F-037)
  [New] BATS tests: 9 new tests for arithmetic validation coverage —
      tlog_read_full non-numeric max_lines (2 tests), tlog_journal_read_full
      max_lines/timeout paths and non-numeric values (5 tests), --status
      corrupt cursor display and false-positive (2 tests) (F-037, F-038)
  [Change] Mock journalctl enhanced with -n flag detection for max_lines
      limit testing
